<div id="outline-container-org7b2cff3" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org7b2cff3"><span class="section-number-2">1.</span> Redis&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;<span class="tag"><span class="database">database</span>&#xa0;<span class="db">db</span>&#xa0;<span class="redis">redis</span></span></h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-1">
<p>
Redis is a in memeory key-value dataabase. Since it is a nosql database it can do a number of things.
</p>

<p>
It is commonly used as a cache system or a task queue.
</p>


<p>
Redis stands for remote dictionary server.
</p>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-orge7aca4a" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orge7aca4a"><span class="section-number-3">1.1.</span> Topics</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-1-1">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><a href="20230330161754-redis_expiration.html#ID-d7ec3a25-ea89-4ab5-ac11-dd4fd05f94a9">redis expiration</a></li>
<li></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org23a4363" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org23a4363"><span class="section-number-3">1.2.</span> Storage and Retrieval</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-1-2">
<p>
Like other key value databases.
All keys are strings.
Data is Accessed by keys.
</p>

<p>
Keys exists in a "key" space (think database)
Single commands are atomic.
</p>
</div>
</div>


<div id="outline-container-org7864da1" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org7864da1"><span class="section-number-3">1.3.</span> Data Types</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-1-3">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org0a182b5" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org0a182b5"><span class="section-number-4">1.3.1.</span> String</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-3-1">
<p>
Normal sequence of bytes. They are binary safe, so they are not null terminated.
</p>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgc6c9eb2" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="orgc6c9eb2"><span class="section-number-4">1.3.2.</span> Hashes</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-3-2">
<p>
Represents a collection of key val pairs
</p>

<p>
The command prefixes start with H
</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>


<div id="outline-container-org8869f88" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org8869f88"><span class="section-number-3">1.4.</span> Commands</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-1-4">
<p>
I will not list all the commands here, just the most used ones
</p>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org3528a28" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org3528a28"><span class="section-number-4">1.4.1.</span> SET</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-4-1">
<p>
Set is used to set a key to a value
</p>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell"><span style="font-weight: bold;">set</span> name foo
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org5ba3bca" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org5ba3bca"><span class="section-number-4">1.4.2.</span> GET</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-4-2">
<p>
Get is used to get a key's value
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">get name
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org64a00be" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org64a00be"><span class="section-number-4">1.4.3.</span> Del</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-4-3">
<p>
Del removes a key
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">del name
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org465d10d" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org465d10d"><span class="section-number-4">1.4.4.</span> GETSET</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-4-4">
<p>
Get a key's value and set a new one
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">getset name foo
</pre>
</div>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">setset name foo1
</pre>
</div>
<p>
If you ran it one more time you would get foo1
</p>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgbd81785" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="orgbd81785"><span class="section-number-4">1.4.5.</span> SETNX</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-1-4-5">
<p>
Set a key if its non existent (is this a lock?)
</p>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">setnx name bar
</pre>
</div>
<p>
#+RESULTS
</p>
<pre class="example">
(integer) 0
</pre>


<p>
See since name exists it failed to set the key
</p>


<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">setnx name1 bar
</pre>
</div>
<p>
#+RESULTS
</p>
<pre class="example">
(integer) 1
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>


<div id="outline-container-orgdf56175" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="orgdf56175"><span class="section-number-3">1.5.</span> Atomic Commands</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-1-5">
<p>
A atomic command is one that can take multiple keys and values and do it in a all or fail manner
</p>

<p>
They operate the same except have a m added to the name
so <code>mset</code> would be <code>set</code>.
</p>

<p>
<code>del</code> can take multiple keys
</p>
